ux25AdmnChannelTable.name: ux25AdmnChannelTable
ux25AdmnChannelTable.description: Defines objects for the parameters of an X.25 interface which the administrator can read and set.

ux25AdmnChanneIndex.name: ux25AdmnChanneIndex
ux25AdmnChanneIndex.description: A unique value for each X.25 subnetwork entity in the chassis. The value of this object matches the value of the index of the corresponding X.25 subnetwork entity entry in the entity table of the chassis MIB.

ux25AdmnNetMode.name: ux25AdmnNetMode
ux25AdmnNetMode.description: Selects the network protocol to be used. Default=x2584(3).

ux25AdmnProtocolVersion.name: ux25AdmnProtocolVersion
ux25AdmnProtocolVersion.description: Determines the X.25 protocol version being used on the network. A network mode of X25_LLC overides this field to the 1984 standard. Default=x25ver84(3).

ux25AdmnInterfaceMode.name: ux25AdmnInterfaceMode
ux25AdmnInterfaceMode.description: Indicates the DTE/DCE nature of the link. The DXE parameter is resolved using ISO 8208 for DTE-DTE operation. Default=dteMode(2).

ux25AdmnLowestPVCVal.name: ux25AdmnLowestPVCVal
ux25AdmnLowestPVCVal.description: Low end of the Permanent Virtual Circuit range. If both the Low and High ends of the range are set to 0 there are no PVCs. Default=0.

ux25AdmnHighestPVCVal.name: ux25AdmnHighestPVCVal
ux25AdmnHighestPVCVal.description: High end of the Permanent Virtual Circuit range. If both the Low and High ends of the range are set to 0 there are no PVCs. Default=0.

ux25AdmnChannelLIC.name: ux25AdmnChannelLIC
ux25AdmnChannelLIC.description: Low end of the one-way incoming logical channel. If both Low and High ends of the channel are set to 0, there are no one-way incoming channels. Default=0.

ux25AdmnChannelHIC.name: ux25AdmnChannelHIC
ux25AdmnChannelHIC.description: High end of the one-way incoming logical channel. If both Low and High ends of the channel are set to 0, there are no one-way incoming channels. Default=0.

ux25AdmnChannelLTC.name: ux25AdmnChannelLTC
ux25AdmnChannelLTC.description: Low end of the two-way incoming logical channel. If both Low and High ends of the channel are set to 0, there are no two-way incoming channels. Default=1024.

ux25AdmnChannelHTC.name: ux25AdmnChannelHTC
ux25AdmnChannelHTC.description: High end of the two-way incoming logical channel. If both Low and High ends of the channel are set to 0, there are no two-way incoming channels. Default=1087.

ux25AdmnChannelLOC.name: ux25AdmnChannelLOC
ux25AdmnChannelLOC.description: Low end of the one-way outgoing logical channel. If both Low and High ends of the channel are set to 0, there are no one-way outgoing channels. Default=0.

ux25AdmnChannelHOC.name: ux25AdmnChannelHOC
ux25AdmnChannelHOC.description: High end of the one-way outgoing logical channel. If both Low and High ends of the channel are set to 0, there are no one-way outgoing channels. Default=0.

ux25AdmnClassTable.name: ux25AdmnClassTable
ux25AdmnClassTable.description: Defines objects for the parameters of an X.25 interface which the administrator can read and set.

ux25AdmnClassIndex.name: ux25AdmnClassIndex
ux25AdmnClassIndex.description: A unique value for each X.25 subnetwork entity in the chassis. The value of this object matches the value of the index of the corresponding X.25 subnetwork entity entry in the entity table of the chassis MIB.

ux25AdmnLocMaxThruPutClass.name: ux25AdmnLocMaxThruPutClass
ux25AdmnLocMaxThruPutClass.description: The maximum value of the throughput class Quality of Service parameter which is supported. According to ISO 8208 this parameter is bounded in the range >=3 and <=12 corresponding to a range 75 to 48000 bits/second. The range supported here is 0 to 15 for non-standard X.25 implementations, which use the Throughput Class Window/Packet Parameters (Group II). Default=12.

ux25AdmnRemMaxThruPutClass.name: ux25AdmnRemMaxThruPutClass
ux25AdmnRemMaxThruPutClass.description: The maximum value of the throughput class Quality of Service parameter which is supported. According to ISO 8208 this parameter is bounded in the range >=3 and <=12 corresponding to a range 75 to 48000 bits/second. The range supported here is 0 to 15 for non-standard X.25 implementations, which use the Throughput Class Window/Packet Parameters (Group II). Default=12.

ux25AdmnLocDefThruPutClass.name: ux25AdmnLocDefThruPutClass
ux25AdmnLocDefThruPutClass.description: The default throughput class that is defined for the local-to-remote direction. In some networks, such as TELENET, negotiation of throughput class is constrained to be towards a configured default throughput class. In other PSDNs, this value should be set equal to the value of the Maximum Local Throughput Class. Default=12.

ux25AdmnRemDefThruPutClass.name: ux25AdmnRemDefThruPutClass
ux25AdmnRemDefThruPutClass.description: The default throughput class value defined for remote-to-local direction. In some networks, such as TELENET, negotiation of throughput class is constrained to be towards a configured default throughput class. In other PSDNs, this value should be set equal to the value of the Maximum Remote Throughput Class. Default=12.

ux25AdmnLocMinThruPutClass.name: ux25AdmnLocMinThruPutClass
ux25AdmnLocMinThruPutClass.description: According to ISO 8208, the throughput class parameter is defined in the range of >=3 to <=12. Some PSDNs may provide different mapping, in which case, this parameter is the minimum value. Default=3.

ux25AdmnRemMinThruPutClass.name: ux25AdmnRemMinThruPutClass
ux25AdmnRemMinThruPutClass.description: According to ISO 8208, the throughput class parameter is defined in the range of >=3 to <=12. Some PSDNs may provide different mapping, in which case, this parameter is the minimum value. Default=3.

ux25AdmnThclassNegToDef.name: ux25AdmnThclassNegToDef
ux25AdmnThclassNegToDef.description: Determines if throughput class negotiation will be used for certain network procedures. Default=disable(1).

ux25AdmnThclassType.name: ux25AdmnThclassType
ux25AdmnThclassType.description: Defines which throughput class encodings can be used to assign packet and window sizes. Some implementations of X.25 do not use the X.25 packet and window negotiation and rely on mapping the throughput class to these parameters. Default=noTcType(1).

ux25AdmnThclassWinMap.name: ux25AdmnThclassWinMap
ux25AdmnThclassWinMap.description: The mapping between throughput class and a window parameter. Each number has a range of 1 to 127. Default=3.3.3.3.3.3.3.3.3.3.3.3.3.3.3.3

ux25AdmnThclassPackMap.name: ux25AdmnThclassPackMap
ux25AdmnThclassPackMap.description: The mapping between the throughput class and a packet parameter. Each number has a range of 4 to 12. Default=7.7.7.7.7.7.7.7.7.7.7.7.7.7.7.7

ux25AdmnPacketTable.name: ux25AdmnPacketTable
ux25AdmnPacketTable.description: Defines objects for the parameters of an X.25 interface which the administrator can read and set.

ux25AdmnPacketIndex.name: ux25AdmnPacketIndex
ux25AdmnPacketIndex.description: A unique value for each X.25 subnetwork entity in the chassis. The value of this object matches the value of the index of the corresponding X.25 subnetwork entity entry in the entity table of the chassis MIB.

ux25AdmnPktSequencing.name: ux25AdmnPktSequencing
ux25AdmnPktSequencing.description: Indicates whether modulo 8 or 128 sequence numbering operates on the network. Default=pktSeq8(16).

ux25AdmnLocMaxPktSize.name: ux25AdmnLocMaxPktSize
ux25AdmnLocMaxPktSize.description: Maximum acceptable size of packets in the local-to-remote direction. On an incoming call, a value for the packet size parameter greater than this value will be negotiated down to an acceptable size when the call is accepted. Default=maxPktSz256(8).

ux25AdmnRemMaxPktSize.name: ux25AdmnRemMaxPktSize
ux25AdmnRemMaxPktSize.description: Maximum acceptable size of packets in the remote-to-local direction. On an incoming call, a value for the packet size parameter greater than this value will be negotiated down to an acceptable size when the call is accepted. Default=maxPktSz256(8).

ux25AdmnLocDefPktSize.name: ux25AdmnLocDefPktSize
ux25AdmnLocDefPktSize.description: Specifies the value of the default packet size for the direction local-to-remote, which may be nonstandard, provided the value is agreed between the communicating parties on the LAN or between the DTE and DCE. Default=defPktSz256(8).

ux25AdmnRemDefPktSize.name: ux25AdmnRemDefPktSize
ux25AdmnRemDefPktSize.description: Specifies the value of the default packet size for the direction remote-to-local, which may be nonstandard, provided the value is agreed between the communicating parties on the LAN or between the DTE and DCE. Default=defPktSz256(8).

ux25AdmnLocMaxWinSize.name: ux25AdmnLocMaxWinSize
ux25AdmnLocMaxWinSize.description: Specifies the maximum local window size. NOTE: 127 allowed only for modulo 128 networks. Default=7.

ux25AdmnRemMaxWinSize.name: ux25AdmnRemMaxWinSize
ux25AdmnRemMaxWinSize.description: Specifies the maximum remote window size. NOTE: 127 allowed only for modulo 128 networks. Default=7.

ux25AdmnLocDefWinSize.name: ux25AdmnLocDefWinSize
ux25AdmnLocDefWinSize.description: Specifies the value of the default window size, which may be nonstandard, provided the value is agreed on by all parties on the LAN between the DTE and DCE. NOTE: The sequence numbering scheme affects the range of this parameter. Default=2.

ux25AdmnRemDefWinSize.name: ux25AdmnRemDefWinSize
ux25AdmnRemDefWinSize.description: Specifies the value of the default window size, which may be nonstandard, provided the value is agreed on by all parties on the LAN between the DTE and DCE. NOTE: The sequence numbering scheme affects the range of this parameter. Default=2.

ux25AdmnMaxNSDULimit.name: ux25AdmnMaxNSDULimit
ux25AdmnMaxNSDULimit.description: The default maximum length beyond which concatenation is stopped and data currently held is passed to the Network Service user. Default=256.

ux25AdmnAccNoDiagnostic.name: ux25AdmnAccNoDiagnostic
ux25AdmnAccNoDiagnostic.description: Allow the omission of the diagnostic byte in incoming RESTART, CLEAR and RESET INDICATION packets. Default=disable(1).

ux25AdmnItutClearLen.name: ux25AdmnItutClearLen
ux25AdmnItutClearLen.description: Restrict the length of a CLEAR INDICATION to 5 bytes and a CLEAR CONFIRM to 3 bytes. Default=disable(1).

ux25AdmnDiscNzDiagnostic.name: ux25AdmnDiscNzDiagnostic
ux25AdmnDiscNzDiagnostic.description: Discard all diagnostic packets on a non-zero LCN. Default=disable(1).

ux25AdmnAcceptHexAdd.name: ux25AdmnAcceptHexAdd
ux25AdmnAcceptHexAdd.description: Allow DTE addresses to contain hexadecimal digits. Default=disable(1).

ux25AdmnBarNonPrivilegeListen.name: ux25AdmnBarNonPrivilegeListen
ux25AdmnBarNonPrivilegeListen.description: Disallow a non-privileged user (i.e without superuser privilege) from listening for incoming calls. Default=enable(2).

ux25AdmnIntlAddrRecognition.name: ux25AdmnIntlAddrRecognition
ux25AdmnIntlAddrRecognition.description: Determine whether outgoing international calls are to be accepted. The values and their interpretation are: 1 - International calls are not distinguished. 2 - The DNIC of the called DTE address is examined and compared to that held in the psdn_local members dnic1 and dnic2. A mismatch implies an international call. 3 - International calls are distinguished by having a '1' prefix on the DTE address. 4 - International calls are distinguished by having a '0' prefix on the DTE address. Default=notDistinguished(1).

ux25AdmnDnic.name: ux25AdmnDnic
ux25AdmnDnic.description: This field contains the first four digits of DNIC and is only used when ux25AdmnIntlAddrRecognition is set to examineDnic(2). Note this field must contain exactly four BCD digits. Default=0000.

ux25AdmnIntlPrioritized.name: ux25AdmnIntlPrioritized
ux25AdmnIntlPrioritized.description: Determine whether some prioritizing method is to used for international calls and is used in conjuction with ux25AdmnPrtyEncodeCtrl and ux25AdmnPrtyPktForced value. Default=disable(1).

ux25AdmnPrtyEncodeCtrl.name: ux25AdmnPrtyEncodeCtrl
ux25AdmnPrtyEncodeCtrl.description: Describes how the priority request is to be encoded for this PSDN. Default=x2588(1).

ux25AdmnPrtyPktForcedVal.name: ux25AdmnPrtyPktForcedVal
ux25AdmnPrtyPktForcedVal.description: If this entry is other than prioPktSz1(1) all priority call requests and incoming calls should have the associated packet size parameter forced to this value. Note that the actual packet size is 2 to the power of this parameter. Default=prioPktSz1(1).

ux25AdmnSrcAddrCtrl.name: ux25AdmnSrcAddrCtrl
ux25AdmnSrcAddrCtrl.description: Provide a means to override or set the calling address in outgoing call requests for this PSDN. Default=noSaCntrl(1).

ux25AdmnDbitInAccept.name: ux25AdmnDbitInAccept
ux25AdmnDbitInAccept.description: Defines the action to take when a Call Accept is received with the D-bit set and there is no local D-bit support. Default=clearCall(3).

ux25AdmnDbitOutAccept.name: ux25AdmnDbitOutAccept
ux25AdmnDbitOutAccept.description: Defines the action to take when the remote user sends a Call Accept with the D-bit set when the local user did not request use of the D-bit. Default=clearCall(3).

ux25AdmnDbitInData.name: ux25AdmnDbitInData
ux25AdmnDbitInData.description: Defines the action to take when a data packet is received with the D-bit set and the local user did not request use of the D-bit. Default=clearCall(3).

ux25AdmnDbitOutData.name: ux25AdmnDbitOutData
ux25AdmnDbitOutData.description: Defines the action when the local user send a data packet with the D-bit set, but the remote party has not indicated D-bit support. Default=clearCall(3).

ux25AdmnSubscriberTable.name: ux25AdmnSubscriberTable
ux25AdmnSubscriberTable.description: Defines objects for the parameters of an X.25 interface which the administrator can read and set.

ux25AdmnSubscriberIndex.name: ux25AdmnSubscriberIndex
ux25AdmnSubscriberIndex.description: A unique value for each X.25 subnetwork entity in the chassis. The value of this object matches the value of the index of the corresponding X.25 subnetwork entity entry in the entity table of the chassis MIB.

ux25AdmnSubCugIaoa.name: ux25AdmnSubCugIaoa
ux25AdmnSubCugIaoa.description: Specifies if this DTE subscribes to Closed User Groups with Incoming or Outgoing access. Default=enable(2).

ux25AdmnSubCugPref.name: ux25AdmnSubCugPref
ux25AdmnSubCugPref.description: Specifies if this DTE subscribes to a Preferential Closed User Groups. Default=disable(1).

ux25AdmnSubCugoa.name: ux25AdmnSubCugoa
ux25AdmnSubCugoa.description: Specifies if this DTE subscribes to Closed User Groups with Outgoing access. Default=disable(1).

ux25AdmnSubCugia.name: ux25AdmnSubCugia
ux25AdmnSubCugia.description: Specifies whether or not this DTE subscribes to Closed User Groups with Incoming Access. Default=disable(1).

ux25AdmnCugFormat.name: ux25AdmnCugFormat
ux25AdmnCugFormat.description: The maximum number of Closed User Groups that this DTE subscribes to. This will be one of two ranges: Basic (100 or fewer) or Extended (between 101 and 10000). Default=basic(1).

ux25AdmnBarInCug.name: ux25AdmnBarInCug
ux25AdmnBarInCug.description: Provides the means to force rejection of any incoming calls carrying the Closed User Group optional facility (which is necessary in some networks, such as DDN. When enabled, such calls will be rejected, otherwise incoming Closed User Group facilities are ignored. Default=disable(1).

ux25AdmnSubExtended.name: ux25AdmnSubExtended
ux25AdmnSubExtended.description: Subscribe to extended call packets (Window and Packet size negotiation is permitted). Default=enable(2).

ux25AdmnBarExtended.name: ux25AdmnBarExtended
ux25AdmnBarExtended.description: Treat window and packet size negotiation in incoming packets as a procedure error. Default=disable(1).

ux25AdmnSubFstSelNoRstrct.name: ux25AdmnSubFstSelNoRstrct
ux25AdmnSubFstSelNoRstrct.description: Subscribe to fast select with no restriction on response. Default=enable(2).

ux25AdmnSubFstSelWthRstrct.name: ux25AdmnSubFstSelWthRstrct
ux25AdmnSubFstSelWthRstrct.description: Subscribe to fast select with restriction on response. Default=disable(1).

ux25AdmnAccptRvsChrgng.name: ux25AdmnAccptRvsChrgng
ux25AdmnAccptRvsChrgng.description: Allow incoming calls to specify the reverse charging facility. Default=disable(1).

ux25AdmnSubLocChargePrevent.name: ux25AdmnSubLocChargePrevent
ux25AdmnSubLocChargePrevent.description: Subscribe to local charging prevention. Default=disable(1).

ux25AdmnSubToaNpiFormat.name: ux25AdmnSubToaNpiFormat
ux25AdmnSubToaNpiFormat.description: Subscribe to TOA/NPI Address Format. Default=disable(1).

ux25AdmnBarToaNpiFormat.name: ux25AdmnBarToaNpiFormat
ux25AdmnBarToaNpiFormat.description: Bar incoming call set-up and clearing packets which use the TOA/NPI Address Format. Default=disable(1).

ux25AdmnTimerTable.name: ux25AdmnTimerTable
ux25AdmnTimerTable.description: Defines objects for the parameters of an X.25 interface which the administrator can read and set.

ux25AdmnTimerIndex.name: ux25AdmnTimerIndex
ux25AdmnTimerIndex.description: A unique value for each X.25 subnetwork entity in the chassis. The value of this object matches the value of the index of the corresponding X.25 subnetwork entity entry in the entity table of the chassis MIB.

ux25AdmnAckDelay.name: ux25AdmnAckDelay
ux25AdmnAckDelay.description: The maximum number of ticks (0.1 second units) over which a pending acknowledgement is withheld. Default=5.

ux25AdmnRstrtTime.name: ux25AdmnRstrtTime
ux25AdmnRstrtTime.description: The number of ticks (0.1 second units) for the DTE timer parameter T20, the Restart Request Response Timer. Default=1800.

ux25AdmnCallTime.name: ux25AdmnCallTime
ux25AdmnCallTime.description: The number of ticks (0.1 second units) for the DTE timer parameter T21, the Call Request Response Timer. Default=2000.

ux25AdmnRstTime.name: ux25AdmnRstTime
ux25AdmnRstTime.description: The number of ticks (0.1 second units) for the DTE timer parameter T22, the Reset Request Response Timer. Default=1800.

ux25AdmnClrTime.name: ux25AdmnClrTime
ux25AdmnClrTime.description: The number of ticks (0.1 second units) for the DTE timer parameter T23, the Clear Request Response Timer. Default=1800.

ux25AdmnWinStatTime.name: ux25AdmnWinStatTime
ux25AdmnWinStatTime.description: Related, but does not correspond exactly to the DTE Window Status Transmission Timer, T24. Specifies the number of ticks (0.1 second units) for the maximum time that acknowledgments of data received from the remote transmitter will be witheld. At timer expiration, any witheld acknowledgments will be carried by a X.25 level 3 RNR packet. Default=750.

ux25AdmnWinRotTime.name: ux25AdmnWinRotTime
ux25AdmnWinRotTime.description: The number of ticks (0.1 second units) for the DTE timer parameter T25, the Window Rotation Timer. Default=1500.

ux25AdmnIntrptTime.name: ux25AdmnIntrptTime
ux25AdmnIntrptTime.description: The number of ticks (0.1 second units) for the DTE timer parameter T26, the Interrupt Response Timer. Default=1800.

ux25AdmnIdleValue.name: ux25AdmnIdleValue
ux25AdmnIdleValue.description: The number of ticks (0.1 second units) during which a link level connection associated with no connections will be maintained. If the link is to a WAN then this value should be zero (infinity). This timer is only used with X.25 on a LAN. Default=0.

ux25AdmnConnectValue.name: ux25AdmnConnectValue
ux25AdmnConnectValue.description: Specifies the number of ticks (0.1 second units), over which the DTE/DCE resolution phase be completely implemented in order to prevent the unlikely event that two packet level entities cannot resolve their DTE/DCE nature. When this expires, the link connection will be disconnected and all pending connections aborted. Default=2000.

ux25AdmnRstrtCnt.name: ux25AdmnRstrtCnt
ux25AdmnRstrtCnt.description: The number of ticks (0.1 second units) for the DTE Restart Request Retransmission Count. Default=1.

ux25AdmnRstCnt.name: ux25AdmnRstCnt
ux25AdmnRstCnt.description: The number of ticks (0.1 second units) for the DTE Reset Request Retransmission Count. Default=1.

ux25AdmnClrCnt.name: ux25AdmnClrCnt
ux25AdmnClrCnt.description: The number of ticks (0.1 second units) for the DTE Clear Request Retransmission Count. Default=1.

ux25AdmnLocalDelay.name: ux25AdmnLocalDelay
ux25AdmnLocalDelay.description: The transit delay (in 0.1 second units) attributed to internal processing. Default=5.

ux25AdmnAccessDelay.name: ux25AdmnAccessDelay
ux25AdmnAccessDelay.description: The transit delay (in 0.1 second units) attributed to the effect of the line transmission rate. Default=5.

ux25OperChannelTable.name: ux25OperChannelTable
ux25OperChannelTable.description: Defines objects that report the current parameters used by a running interface. These objects are read only.

ux25OperClassTable.name: ux25OperClassTable
ux25OperClassTable.description: Defines objects that report the current parameters used by a running interface. These objects are read only.

ux25OperPacketTable.name: ux25OperPacketTable
ux25OperPacketTable.description: Defines objects that report the current parameters used by a running interface. These objects are read only.

ux25OperSubscriberTable.name: ux25OperSubscriberTable
ux25OperSubscriberTable.description: Defines objects that report the current parameters used by a running interface. These objects are read only.

ux25OperTimerTable.name: ux25OperTimerTable
ux25OperTimerTable.description: Defines objects that report the current parameters used by a running interface. These objects are read only.

ux25StatTable.name: ux25StatTable
ux25StatTable.description: Defines objects that report operational statistics for an X.25 interface.

ux25StatIndex.name: ux25StatIndex
ux25StatIndex.description: A unique value for each X.25 subnetwork entity in the chassis. The value of this object matches the value of the index of the corresponding X.25 subnetwork entity entry in the entity table of the chassis MIB.

ux25StatRcvrNotRdyRcvd.name: ux25StatRcvrNotRdyRcvd
ux25StatRcvrNotRdyRcvd.description: Number of receiver not ready received.

ux25StatRcvrNotRdySent.name: ux25StatRcvrNotRdySent
ux25StatRcvrNotRdySent.description: Number of receiver not ready sent.

ux25StatPVCsInDatTrnsfrState.name: ux25StatPVCsInDatTrnsfrState
ux25StatPVCsInDatTrnsfrState.description: Number of PVCs in Data Transfer State.

ux25StatSVCsInDatTrnsfrState.name: ux25StatSVCsInDatTrnsfrState
ux25StatSVCsInDatTrnsfrState.description: Number of SVCs in Data Transfer State.
